boData.longDescription:
The account debt monitor analyzes all accounts whose C&C review date is on or before the supplied business date. For more information about the account debt monitor, launch the online help and navigate to the index entry "credit & collections, monitoring overdue debt".
The input parameter controls how the trigger date is set on collection events that are created by this process. For more information about date arithmetic options, launch the online help and navigate to the index entry "calendar,calendar days versus work days".
This process is multi-threaded. Records between commits: 100 Minutes between cursor re-initiation: 15
This process supports creating To Do entries for object specific errors. For more information, launch the online help and navigate to the index entry "background processes, processing errors".

batchControlParameter.longDescription: Enter a value here to filter by CIS Division.
Enter a value here to override the maximum number of errors allowed before the run is terminated.
Thread pool name to use if the DEFAULT thread pool is not desired.
